{"author":{"id":"1949ffc23f11a8cb4f8c42a45c9ad241b49570df9a18687489e9ea78d87c54a3"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1772048183,"nonce":"fPQJXfeCFJyEGpJheiwUJS4JZ0I=","title":"MJXPlant: MuJoCo/MJX as a feedbax plant","message":"[Imported from GitHub #52] (created 2026-02-21T23:28:08Z)\n\n## Motivation\n\nfeedbax's analytical plants (TwoLinkArm, PointMass) are limited in realism. MuJoCo provides high-fidelity physics (contacts, tendons, complex actuators) and MJX (its JAX backend) makes it vmap/jit-compatible for GPU-parallel simulation.\n\nAn MJXPlant would give feedbax access to arbitrary MuJoCo models while staying in the JAX ecosystem.\n\n## Design\n\nMJXPlant wraps `mjx.step()` as a discrete-step plant. Unlike analytical plants that provide `vector_field()` for Diffrax integration, MJX IS the solver — it steps the physics directly.\n\nKey components:\n- `MJXPlant`: wraps `mjx.Model` + `mjx.Data`, provides `step()`, `init()`, effector extraction\n- Constructed from `BodyPreset → MJCF XML → mujoco.MjModel → mjx.Model`\n- Compatible with RL training (step-based rollouts) and graph composition\n- First-order muscle activation dynamics (tau_act/tau_deact) applied before physics step\n\n## Interface Questions\n\nMJX doesn't fit `AbstractDynamicalSystem.vector_field()` since it's a discrete stepper, not a continuous ODE. Options:\n1. Broader plant abstraction supporting both continuous and discrete dynamics\n2. MJXPlant as a parallel abstraction alongside AbstractPlant\n3. Wrapper that exposes MJX as approximate `vector_field()` for Diffrax (lossy)\n\nSee #50 (alternative training methods) for the training-side implications.\n\n## Dependencies\n\n- feedbax #51: configurable body parameterization (BodyPreset → model construction)\n- feedbax #50: RL training infrastructure (primary consumer of step-based dynamics)\n- `mujoco-mjx` package dependency\n\nCo-authored-by: Claude Opus 4.6 \u003cnoreply@anthropic.com\u003e","files":null}]}